@flexiarg enrichment/layered-ingestion
@title Layered Ingestion Architecture
@sigils [节/引]
@keywords layer, ingestion, topology, provenance, evidence, tension, dependency, phase
@audience futon developers, enrichment operators
@tone technical
@factor Keen investigation (dhammavicaya)
@references [p4ng/reflect-in-layers iching/hexagram-53-jian enrichment/ARGUMENT]

! conclusion:
  Structure enrichment as six layers (L0-L5) where each layer addresses one
  enrichment concern and depends on the previous layer being verified.

  + context: The code browser needs six kinds of enrichment data: docs
    (existing), mission provenance, pattern provenance, evidence binding,
    tension surface, and cross-futon dependencies. Ingesting all six at once
    would be fragile (errors in topology corrupt provenance) and unverifiable
    (too many moving parts to check).
  + IF:
    Six enrichment concerns need to be ingested into the hyperedge store,
    each with different data sources and validation criteria.
  + HOWEVER:
    Later layers depend on earlier layers being correct (mission provenance
    references namespaces from L0; evidence binding references missions from
    L1). Ingesting them simultaneously means errors cascade silently.
  + THEN:
    Six layers, each verified before the next:
    L0: Namespace topology + complexity + churn (structural ground truth)
    L1: Mission provenance (var → mission, from mission docs + git blame)
    L2: Pattern provenance (var → pattern, from PSR/PUR evidence)
    L3: Evidence binding (var → evidence entries)
    L4: Tension surface (var → invariant violations)
    L5: Cross-futon dependencies (var → var across repos)
  + BECAUSE:
    The reflect-in-layers [节] pattern says layered reflection builds shared
    understanding. Each layer is a checkpoint: verify L0 topology before
    attempting L1 provenance. Hexagram-53 [引] says durable change is built
    incrementally. The dependency chain (L0→L1→...→L5) makes each step
    small enough to review and correct independently.
  + NEXT-STEPS:
    - evidence: Layer 0 verified (namespace count matches reflection API)
    - evidence: Layer 1 verified (every var→mission edge traceable to a
      mission doc or git blame commit)
    - evidence: replay query showing L0→L1 growth in XTDB
